<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-10T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-10T13:36:00-05:00" n="355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24830: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-10T12:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">January 10,
                                        1921—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 6:37
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. Local press publishes Foreign Office statement that Ecuador has
                            recognized Mexican Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>